Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A clock and data recovery method, comprising: recovering a first clock signal from transitions between pairs of symbols representative of successive signaling states of a 3-wire interface, wherein each pair of symbols includes a first symbol and a second symbol, and wherein a pulse in the first clock signal is generated in response to an earliest-occurring transition at a boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol detected in one of three difference signals that represent difference in signaling state between two wires of the 3-wire interface; determining direction of voltage change of a first transition detected on a first difference signal at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol; providing a value selected based on the direction of voltage change of the first transition as value of the first difference signal in the second symbol; and providing a value of a second difference signal captured during the first symbol as the value of the second difference signal in the second symbol when the second difference signal does not transition at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol. 2. The method of claim 1, further comprising: coupling the first difference signal to a first edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a first direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; coupling the first difference signal to a second edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a second direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; and determining the direction of voltage change of the first transition based on outputs of the first edge-triggered flipflop and the second edge-triggered flipflop. 3. The method of claim 2, wherein coupling the first difference signal to the first edge-triggered flipflop comprises: delaying the first difference signal. 4. The method of claim 2, wherein coupling the first difference signal to the second edge-triggered flipflop comprises: delaying the first difference signal; and inverting the first difference signal. 5. The method of claim 2, further comprising: using the first clock signal to capture output of the state of the first edge-triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol; and using the first clock signal to capture output of the state of the second edge- triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol. 6. The method of claim 2, further comprising: using the first clock signal to capture the value of the first difference signal in the second symbol. 7. The method of claim 1, wherein at least one wire of the 3 -wire interface changes state between the first symbol and the second symbol. 8. A clock and data recovery apparatus, comprising: a plurality of difference receivers configured to provide difference signals, each difference signal representative of a difference in signaling state between a pair of wires in a 3-wire interface; a clock recovery circuit configured to generate a pulse in a first clock signal in response to an earliest-occurring transition detected in one of the difference signals at a boundary between a first symbol and a second symbol; a first set of flipflops including a first flipflop that detects positive-going transitions in a first difference signal, and a second flipflop that detects negative-going transitions in the first difference signal; and a selection circuit configured to: determine direction of voltage change of a first transition detected in the first difference signal at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol, wherein the direction of voltage change is determined using the first flipflop and the second flipflop; 

 provide a value selected based on the direction of voltage change of the first transition as value of the first difference signal in the second symbol; and provide a value of a second difference signal captured during the first symbol as the value of the second difference signal in the second symbol when the second difference signal does not transition at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol. 9. The clock and data recovery apparatus of claim 8, wherein the first flipflop is configured to change state when the first transition comprises a transition from logic zero to logic one and the second flipflop is configured to change state when the first transition comprises a transition from logic one to logic zero. 10. The clock and data recovery apparatus of claim 8, further comprising: a plurality of delay circuits configured to couple the difference signals to the first set of flipflops such that the first flipflop and the second flipflop receive a delayed version of the first difference signal. 11. The clock and data recovery apparatus of claim 10, wherein the first flipflop and the second flipflop receive an inverted version of the first difference signal. 12. The clock and data recovery apparatus of claim 8, further comprising: a second set of flipflops configured to capture outputs of the first set of flipflops using the pulse in the first clock signal; and a third set of flipflops configured to capture values of the difference signals using the pulse in the first clock signal. 13. The clock and data recovery apparatus of claim 8, wherein at least one wire of the 3-wire interface changes state between the first symbol and the second symbol. 14. An apparatus comprising: means for recovering a first clock signal from transitions between pairs of symbols representative of successive signaling states of a 3-wire interface, wherein each pair of symbols includes a first symbol and a second symbol, and wherein a pulse in the first 

 clock signal is generated in response to an earliest-occurring transition at a boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol detected in one of three difference signals that represent difference in signaling state between two wires of the 3-wire interface; means for determining direction of voltage change of a first transition detected on a first difference signal at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol; means for providing a value selected based on the direction of the voltage change of the first transition as value of the first difference signal in the second symbol; and means for providing a value of a second difference signal captured during the first symbol as the value of the second difference signal in the second symbol when the second difference signal does not transition at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol. 15. The apparatus of claim 14, wherein the means for determining the direction of the voltage change of the first transition is operative to: couple the first difference signal to a first edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a first direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; couple the first difference signal to a second edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a second direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; and determine the direction of voltage change of the first transition based on outputs of the first edge-triggered flipflop and the second edge-triggered flipflop. 16. The apparatus of claim 15, further comprising: a delay circuit configured to delay the first difference signal such that a delayed first difference signal is provided to the first edge-triggered flipflop and the second edge- triggered flipflop. 17. The apparatus of claim 16, wherein the delay circuit is adapted to invert the first difference signal to obtain the delayed first difference signal. 18. The apparatus of claim 15, wherein the first clock signal is used to capture output of the state of the first edge-triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol and 

 output of the state of the second edge-triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol. 19. The apparatus of claim 15, wherein the first clock signal is used to capture the value of the first difference signal in the second symbol. 20. The apparatus of claim 14, wherein at least one wire of the 3-wire interface changes state between the first symbol and the second symbol. 21. A processor-readable storage medium having one or more instructions which, when executed by at least one processor of a processing circuit, cause the processing circuit to: recover a first clock signal from transitions between pairs of symbols representative of successive signaling states of a 3-wire interface, wherein each pair of symbols includes a first symbol and a second symbol, and wherein a pulse in the first clock signal is generated in response to an earliest-occurring transition at a boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol detected in one of three difference signals that represent difference in signaling state between two wires of the 3-wire interface; determine direction of voltage change of a first transition detected on a first difference signal at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol; provide a value selected based on the direction of voltage change of the first transition as value of the first difference signal in the second symbol; and provide a value of a second difference signal captured during the first symbol as the value of the second difference signal in the second symbol when the second difference signal does not transition at the boundary between the first symbol and the second symbol. 22. The storage medium of claim 21, wherein the one or more instructions further cause the processing circuit to: couple the first difference signal to a first edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a first direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; 

 couple the first difference signal to a second edge-triggered flipflop that changes state when the first transition is characterized by a second direction of voltage change of the first difference signal; and determine the direction of voltage change of the first transition based on outputs of the first edge-triggered flipflop and the second edge-triggered flipflop. 23. The storage medium of claim 22, wherein the first difference signal is delayed by a delay circuit when coupled to the first edge-triggered flipflop. 24. The storage medium of claim 22, wherein the first difference signal is inverted when coupled to the first edge-triggered flipflop. 25. The storage medium of claim 22, wherein the first clock signal is used to capture output of the state of the first edge-triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol and output of the state of the second edge-triggered flipflop during transmission of the first symbol. 26. The storage medium of claim 22, wherein the first clock signal is used to capture the value of the first difference signal in the second symbol. 27. The storage medium of claim 21, wherein at least one wire of the 3 -wire interface changes state between the first symbol and the second symbol.
